### Checks

- [X] I have checked that this issue has not already been reported.

- [X] I have confirmed this bug exists on the [latest version](https://crates.io/crates/polars) of Polars.


### Reproducible example

```rust

////////////////////Trying with Scan Parquet in Polars//////////////////////////////////////////////
let start = Instant::now();
const TEST_S3: &str = "azure://test-func/10003.parquet";
let AccountName = "blobstore";
let AccountKey = "blobkey";
let cloud_options=cloud::CloudOptions::default().with_azure([(Key::AccountName,AccountName),(Key::AccessKey,AccountKey)]);

let mut args = ScanArgsParquet::default();
args.parallel = ParallelStrategy::RowGroups;
args.cloud_options = Some(cloud_options);

let df_blob = LazyFrame::scan_parquet(TEST_S3, args)?
        .with_streaming(true)
        .select([
            // select all columns
            all(),
        ])
        .collect()?;
    //
    let duration_row_mapping = start.elapsed();

    println!("Time elapsed in reading blob data is: {:?}", duration_row_mapping);

    //Time elapsed in reading blob data is: 3.387758s

///////////////////////Trying Directly with MicrosoftAzure Builder/////////////////////////////////////////////////////
let STORAGE_ACCOUNT = ""blobstore";
let KEY = "blobkey";
let CONTAINER_NAME = "test-func"
const INPUT_LOCATION: &str = "10003.parquet";

let start = Instant::now();

let object_store = MicrosoftAzureBuilder::new()
	.with_account(STORAGE_ACCOUNT)
	.with_container_name(CONTAINER_NAME)
	.with_access_key(KEY)
	.build()?;

let data = object_store.get(&Path::from(INPUT_LOCATION)).await?;

let df = ParquetReader::new(std::io::Cursor::new(data.bytes().await?)).read_parallel(ParallelStrategy::RowGroups).finish().unwrap();

let duration_row_mapping = start.elapsed();

println!("Time elapsed in reading blob data is: {:?}", duration_row_mapping)

//Time elapsed in reading blob data is: 1.7203642s



```
 

### Log output

_No response_

### Issue description

LazyFrame::Scan_Parquet does not seem to offer the expected efficiency when reading from Azure Blob Storage. Its performs worse than ParquetReader when reading file of the same size from Azure Blob Storage.

### Expected behavior

It should be atleast equal in terms of performance to the "ParquetReader" if not better if you are reading a whole file without filtering.

### Installed versions

<details>

polars = { version = "0.34.1", features = ["serde", "json", "polars-io","rank", "lazy","azure","dtype-struct","parquet","streaming","cloud"] }
object_store = "0.7.1"
</details>
